data.people_bio:
Bogyoke Aung San served as the 5th Premier of the British Crown Colony of Burma from 1946 to 1947. Initially he was a communist and later a social democratic politician. Wikipedia
Born: February 13, 1915, Natmauk
Died: July 19, 1947, Yangon
Political party: Anti-Fascist People's Freedom League; Communist Party of Burma
Spouse: Khin Kyi (m. 1942–1947)
Cause of death: Assassination
Books: The Political Legacy of Aung San
Children: Aung San Suu Kyi, Aung San Oo, Aung San Lin, Aung San Chit
